The Coordinator Anambra State Keke Drivers Forum, Comrade Osita Obi, has drawn the attention of members of the public to the random arrest of 11 Keke Drivers at Unizik Tem Site, Awka, where the drivers were sensitising their colleagues about Governor Soludo’s new tax system which commenced July 1, this year. Obi in a public notice made available to our correspondent, said that the 11 union members of Keke Drivers arrested by the policelastweekFridayatUnizik TemSite, Awka, were still in custody at the State Criminal Investigation Department, Awka, pointing out that police alleged that the KekeDriverswerebearingarms and dangerous weapons. Hesaid oneCollinsOzorjiofor aka Snoop who used to intimidate Keke Drivers into giving him and his cronies government revenues from Keke, had stormed where the union leaders were educating their members on the new E-Revenue System of the government and was resisted but later connived with B Division police operatives to make random arrest in the area. The Coordinator’s public notice reads, “The Anambra State Keke Drivers Forum writes to draw the attention of the following authorities, the Governor, the Commissioner for Transport, the Commissioner for Homeland Security, the Chief Security Adviser to the governor, the Commissioner of Police, the Director of State Security (DSS) and the public to the continued intimidation, harassment, exploitation and extortion of keke drivers by Collins Ozojiofor alas Snoop in connivance with the Anambra State Police Command. “Collins Ozojiofor alias Snoop, his gang and some policemen arrested some keke drivers at Unizik Tem site junction who were sensitising fellow keke drivers on the new Anambra State biometric data registration for keke drivers.